Compiling world data set

GV900 Political Explanation

Daina Chiba

02 October, 2019

Abstract

This file compiles a cross-national data set to be used in R tutorials.

Preparation

We first build a cross-national data frame.

library(tidyverse)
library(haven)
library(readxl)
library(countrycode)
library(states)
library(rworldmap)

# colors
red <- "#ca0020"; blue <- "#0571b0"; green <- "#4daf4a"
brown <- "#b09a05"; orange <- "#ca4500"; green2 <- "#00caaa"
purple <- "#b00571"

Lets first create a blank data set that contains all the countries in the Gleditsch-Ward list (excluding microstates).

# Load country lists
data(gwstates)
# Create crossnational data for 2017
sp <- as.tibble(state_panel(start = "2017-01-01", end = "2017-12-31"))
sp <- left_join(sp, gwstates) %>% 
  filter(microstate==FALSE) %>% 
  select(gwcode, country_name)
sp <- unique(sp)
sp $ year <- 2017
sp

Lets assign COW country code and ISO numeric code.

# COW code
sp $ cowc <- countrycode(sp$country_name, 
  origin="country.name", destination="cown")

# Missing COW code?
sp %>% filter(is.na(cowc))
# A tibble: 3 x 4
  gwcode country_name                     year  cowc
   <int> <chr>                           <dbl> <int>
1    340 Serbia                           2017    NA
2    731 Korea, People's Republic of      2017    NA
3    816 Vietnam, Democratic Republic of  2017    NA
sp $ cowc[sp $ gwcode==731] <- countrycode("North Korea",
  origin="country.name", destination="cown")
sp $ cowc[sp $ gwcode==816] <- countrycode("Vietnam",
  origin="country.name", destination="cown")
sp <- sp %>% filter(is.na(cowc)==FALSE)

# ISO code
sp $ iso3c <- countrycode(sp$gwcode, 
  origin="gwn", destination="iso3c")

# Missing ISO code?
sp %>% filter(is.na(iso3c))
# A tibble: 3 x 5
  gwcode country_name                     year  cowc iso3c
   <int> <chr>                           <dbl> <int> <chr>
1    347 Kosovo                           2017   347 <NA> 
2    678 Yemen (Arab Republic of Yemen)   2017   678 <NA> 
3    816 Vietnam, Democratic Republic of  2017   817 <NA> 
sp $ iso3c[sp $ gwcode==678] <- countrycode("Yemen", 
  origin="country.name", destination="iso3c")
sp $ iso3c[sp $ gwcode==816] <- countrycode("Vietnam", 
  origin="country.name", destination="iso3c")
sp <- sp %>% filter(is.na(iso3c)==FALSE)
sp <- sp %>% select(gwcode, cowc, iso3c, everything())

Regions

Lets classify countries into geographical regions.

# Regions
sp $ region <- countrycode(sp $ cowc, origin = "cown", destination = "region")
sp[is.na(sp$region),]
# A tibble: 1 x 6
  gwcode  cowc iso3c country_name                    year region
   <int> <int> <chr> <chr>                          <dbl> <chr> 
1    678   678 YEM   Yemen (Arab Republic of Yemen)  2017 <NA>  
sp $ region[sp $ cowc == 678] <- "Western Asia"

sp $ region7 <- NA
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Western Africa" | 
    sp $ region == "Eastern Africa" | 
    sp $ region == "Southern Africa" | 
    sp $ region == "Middle Africa"] <- "Africa"
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Eastern Europe" | 
    sp $ region == "Central Asia" ] <- "Eastern Europe and Central Asia"
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Caribbean" | 
    sp $ region == "Central America" | 
    sp $ region == "South America"] <- "Latin America and the Caribbean"
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Western Asia" | 
    sp $ region == "Northern Africa"] <- "Middle East and North Africa"
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Southern Asia" | 
    sp $ region == "South-Eastern Asia"] <- "South Asia"
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Eastern Asia" | 
    sp $ region == "Polynesia" | 
    sp $ region == "Melanesia" | 
    sp $ region == "Micronesia"] <- "East Asia and the Pacific"
sp $ region7[sp $ region == "Northern Europe" | 
    sp $ region == "Western Europe" | 
    sp $ region == "Southern Europe" | 
    sp $ region == "Northern America" | 
    sp $ region == "Australia and New Zealand"] <- "Western Europe and other developed countries"

Ethnic fractionalization data

Alesina, Alberto, Arnaud Devleeschauwer, William Easterly, Sergio Kurlat, and Romain Wacziarg. 2003. Fractionalization. Journal of Economic Growth 8 (June): 155-194.

https://nsd.no/macrodataguide/set.html?id=16&sub=1

ef <- read_excel("2003_fractionalization.xls", skip = 1, na = ".")
ef <- ef[2:216, ]
ef <- ef %>% select(Country, Ethnic, Language, Religion)
ef$Ethnic <- as.numeric(ef$Ethnic)
ef$Language <- as.numeric(ef$Language)
ef$Religion <- as.numeric(ef$Religion)
ef <- ef %>% rename(frac_eth = Ethnic, frac_lan = Language, frac_rel = Religion)
ef$cowc <- countrycode(ef$Country, origin = "country.name", destination = "cown")

# Omit cases where COW code is missing
ef %>% filter(is.na(cowc))

Create categorical variables for fractionalization variables.

# Ethnic fractionalization
ef.cuts <- sp$frac_eth %>% quantile(c(1/3, 2/3), na.rm = TRUE)
sp$frac_eth3 <- ifelse(sp$frac_eth < ef.cuts[1], "Low", ifelse(sp$frac_eth < 
    ef.cuts[2], "Medium", "High"))
sp$frac_eth3 <- ordered(sp$frac_eth3, levels = c("High", "Medium", "Low"), labels = c("High", 
    "Medium", "Low"))

# Linguistic fractionalization
lf.cuts <- sp$frac_lan %>% quantile(c(1/3, 2/3), na.rm = TRUE)
sp$frac_lan3 <- ifelse(sp$frac_lan < lf.cuts[1], "Low", ifelse(sp$frac_lan < 
    lf.cuts[2], "Medium", "High"))

# Religious fractionalization
rf.cuts <- sp$frac_rel %>% quantile(c(1/3, 2/3), na.rm = TRUE)
sp$frac_rel3 <- ifelse(sp$frac_rel < rf.cuts[1], "Low", ifelse(sp$frac_rel < 
    rf.cuts[2], "Medium", "High"))

sp <- sp %>% select(gwcode, cowc, iso3c, country_name, frac_eth, frac_eth3, 
    frac_lan, frac_lan3, frac_rel, frac_rel3, everything())
sp

Religion

http://www.correlatesofwar.org/data-sets/world-religion-data

wrp <- read_csv("WRP_national.csv")
wrp <- wrp %>% filter(year == 2010) %>% select(state, contains("genpct"), nonreligpct)

wrp_cols <- wrp %>% select(chrstgenpct:nonreligpct) %>% names()
wrp <- wrp %>% mutate(max = pmax(!!!rlang::syms(wrp_cols)))

names(wrp)
 [1] "state"       "chrstgenpct" "judgenpct"   "islmgenpct"  "budgenpct"  
 [6] "zorogenpct"  "hindgenpct"  "sikhgenpct"  "shntgenpct"  "bahgenpct"  
[11] "taogenpct"   "jaingenpct"  "confgenpct"  "syncgenpct"  "anmgenpct"  
[16] "othrgenpct"  "nonreligpct" "max"        
wrp$religion <- "Christianity"
wrp$religion <- ifelse(wrp$chrstgenpct == wrp$max, "Christianity", ifelse(wrp$islmgenpct == 
    wrp$max, "Islam", ifelse(wrp$judgenpct == wrp$max, "Judaism", ifelse(wrp$budgenpct == 
    wrp$max, "Budhism", ifelse(wrp$zorogenpct == wrp$max, "Zoro", ifelse(wrp$hindgenpct == 
    wrp$max, "Hinduism", ifelse(wrp$sikhgenpct == wrp$max, "Sikh", ifelse(wrp$nonreligpct == 
    wrp$max, "Nonreligious", "Other"))))))))

Heritage foundation data

https://www.heritage.org/index/explore

hf <- read_csv("heritage.csv")
hf <- hf %>% rename(property_rights = "property rights", government_integrity = "government integrity", 
    judicial_effectiveness = "judicial effectiveness", tax_burden = "tax burden", 
    government_spending = "government spending", fiscal_health = "fiscal health", 
    business_freedom = "business freedom", labor_freedom = "labor freedom", 
    monetary_freedom = "monetary freedom", trade_freedom = "trade freedom", 
    investment_freedom = "investment freedom", financial_freedom = "financial freedom")
hf <- hf %>% select(-"index year")
hf$cowc <- countrycode(hf$name, origin = "country.name", destination = "cown")
hf <- hf %>% select(-"overall score")
hf <- hf %>% select(-name)
hf <- hf %>% filter(is.na(hf$cowc) == FALSE)
sp <- left_join(sp, hf)
sp <- sp %>% select(-year)

ILO

https://ilostat.ilo.org/data/bulk/

Trade union density (latest available data during 2005-2016)

union <- read_csv("ILR_TUMT_NOC_RT_A.csv")
unmy <- union %>% select(ref_area, time, obs_value) %>% group_by(ref_area) %>% 
    slice(which.max(time))
unmy$cowc <- countrycode(unmy$ref_area, origin = "iso3c", destination = "cown")

unmy <- unmy %>% select(cowc, obs_value) %>% filter(is.na(cowc) == FALSE) %>% 
    rename(union = obs_value)
unmy$ref_area <- NULL
sp <- left_join(sp, unmy)

UNDP

http://hdr.undp.org/en/data

Per capita GDP (2011 PPP)

gdppc <- read_csv("UNDP/GDP per capita (2011 PPP $).csv", skip = 1)
gdppc <- gdppc %>% select(Country, "2017")
gdppc <- gdppc %>% rename(gdppc = "2017")

GDP (total, 2011 PPP in billions)

gdp <- read_csv("UNDP/Gross domestic product (GDP), total (2011 PPP $ billions).csv", 
    skip = 1)
gdp <- gdp %>% select(Country, "2017")
gdp <- gdp %>% rename(gdp = "2017")

GINI

gini <- read_csv("UNDP/Income inequality, Gini coefficient.csv", skip = 1)
gini <- gini %>% select(Country, "2010-2017")
gini <- gini %>% rename(gini = "2010-2017")

Mean years of schooling

sch <- read_csv("UNDP/Mean years of schooling (years).csv", skip = 1)
sch <- sch %>% select(Country, "2017")
sch <- sch %>% rename(school = "2017")

Total population (millions)

pop <- read_csv("UNDP/Total population (millions).csv", skip = 1)
pop <- pop %>% select(Country, "2017")
pop <- pop %>% rename(pop = "2017")

Unemployment

unemp <- read_csv("UNDP/Unemployment, total (% of labour force).csv", skip = 1)
unemp <- unemp %>% select(Country, "2017")
unemp <- unemp %>% rename(unemp = "2017")

Old

old <- read_csv("UNDP/Population ages 65 and older (millions).csv", skip = 1)
old <- old %>% select(Country, "2017")
old <- old %>% rename(old = "2017")

Merge them

undp <- left_join(gdppc, gdp)
undp <- left_join(undp, gini)
undp <- left_join(undp, sch)
undp <- left_join(undp, pop)
undp <- left_join(undp, unemp)
undp <- left_join(undp, old)
undp$Country[44] <- "Corte d'Ivoire"
undp$cowc <- countrycode(undp$Country, origin = "country.name", destination = "cown")
undp$Country[is.na(undp$cowc)] %>% head()
[1] "Eswatini (Kingdom of)"  "Hong Kong, China (SAR)"
[3] "Palestine, State of"    "Serbia"                
[5] NA                       NA                      
undp <- undp %>% select(-Country)
undp <- undp %>% filter(is.na(undp$cowc) == FALSE)
sp <- left_join(sp, undp)

   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.    NA's 
    0.0    14.0    20.6    22.2    31.0    61.3       2 
# Lower chamber electoral system
pr <- as.tibble(data.frame(country_name = vd2$country_name, prsys = NA))
pr <- pr %>% filter(country_name != "Palestine/Gaza")

for (i in 1:nrow(pr)) {
    vdp <- vd %>% select(country_name, year, v2elparlel) %>% filter(country_name == 
        pr$country_name[i])
    j <- 2018
    while (is.na(pr$prsys[i]) == TRUE & j >= max(1900, min(vdp$year))) {
        pr$prsys[i] <- vdp$v2elparlel[vdp$year == j]
        j <- j - 1
    }
}

pr$pr <- NA
pr$pr[pr$prsys == 1 | pr$prsys == 2] <- "Yes"
pr$pr[pr$prsys == 0 | pr$prsys == 3] <- "No"
pr <- pr %>% select(country_name, pr)
pr$pr <- as.factor(pr$pr)

vd3 <- vd2 %>% select(country_name, v2lgfemleg)
vd3 <- left_join(vd3, pr)
vd3$cowc <- countrycode(vd3$country_name, origin = "country.name", destination = "cown")
vd3 <- vd3 %>% filter(is.na(cowc) == FALSE) %>% select(cowc, v2lgfemleg, pr)
sp <- left_join(sp, vd3)
names(sp)[names(sp) == "v2lgfemleg"] <- "femalerep"

p4 <- read_excel("p4v2017.xls")
p4 <- p4 %>% filter(year == 2017) %>% select(ccode, polity2)
p4 <- p4 %>% rename(cowc = ccode)

# Create a categorical variable
p4$polity2_cat3 <- NA
p4$polity2_cat3[p4$polity2 >= 6] <- "Democracy"
p4$polity2_cat3[p4$polity2 <= -6] <- "Autocracy"
p4$polity2_cat3[p4$polity2 >= -5 & p4$polity2 <= 5] <- "Anocracy"
p4$polity2_cat3 <- ordered(p4$polity2_cat3, levels = c("Autocracy", "Anocracy", 
    "Democracy"))
sp <- left_join(sp, p4)

bmr <- read_csv("democracy-v3.0.csv")
bmr <- bmr %>% filter(year == 2015) %>% select(ccode, democracy)
bmr <- bmr %>% rename(cowc = ccode)
bmr$democ_bmr <- ifelse(bmr$democracy == 1, "Democracy", "Non-Democracy")
bmr <- bmr %>% select(cowc, democ_bmr)
